CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, p. A3, reads: "Large Room - More than 200 Masons, together with more than 200 members and friends of Loendi, gathered in this area, as indoor ceremonies were conducted. The space, when completed will be the main dining room of the club, and will also serve as a banquet hall, ballroom and general assembly. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Masons wearing aprons and chain collars, holding ceremonial poles and banner, with other men and women holding Loendi Club brochures, in Loendi Club for cornerstone laying ceremonies
